messages.content: 'Things are good, thanks. Busy day at work, but it's all worth it. How about you?'
messages.speaker: CIVILIAN_greek_civilian_Worker-btBf6jqNf60

messages.content: I don't need to show you my ID. I know why you're here, and I don't want your kind in Greece. We don't need your army interfering in our affairs. Leave now before it escalates further.
messages.speaker: CIVILIAN_greek_civilian_Worker-btBf6jqNf60

messages.content: You're not welcome here, Blufor. You come to our country, invade our land, and now you want to talk to me? I have nothing to say to you.
messages.speaker: CIVILIAN_greek_civilian_Worker-btBf6jqNf60

messages.content: Damn, that's quite hostile! you forget I am the one with the gun
messages.speaker: BLUFOR_english_PRIVATE_Autorifleman-1hGanXhhpro

messages.content: I understand that you have been sent here to do a job, but my loyalty lies with my country and my people. We may not have much, but we have our pride and our traditions. I will not help you find anyone who may be considered a traitor to our cause.
messages.speaker: CIVILIAN_greek_civilian_Worker-btBf6jqNf60

messages.content: Tally, you are not welcome here in Greece. This is our home and we do not want foreign soldiers here. Leave our country and take your violence with you.
messages.speaker: CIVILIAN_greek_civilian_Worker-btBf6jqNf60
